<heading id="D0A196454B1AFF9414F9D785FDD3F918" box="[136,563,1756,1783]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1AFF9414F9D785FE7AF918" authority="Miller (1768" authorityName="Miller, Herb. Clifford" authorityYear="1768" box="[136,410,1756,1783]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1AFF9414F9D785FEE1F919" bold="true" box="[136,257,1756,1783]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Abies alba</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1AFF941579D785FE7AF918" author="Miller, P." box="[264,410,1756,1782]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" refId="ref10389" refString="Miller, P. (1768) The gardeners dictionary, eighth edition. John and Frances Rivington, London, 1300 pp." type="book" year="1768">Miller (1768</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: Abies No. 1)
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34C72A24B1AFF9714F9D67DFDECFBD3" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE921294B1AFF9414F9D67DFBA7F868" blockId="1.[136,1452,1828,2071]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
When describing 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1AFF94153ED67DFDD4F8D1" authority=", Miller (1768)" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[335,564,1828,1855]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1AFF94153ED67DFE6DF8D0" box="[335,397,1828,1854]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Abies</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1AFF9415EDD67DFDD4F8D1" author="Miller, P." box="[412,564,1828,1855]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" refId="ref10389" refString="Miller, P. (1768) The gardeners dictionary, eighth edition. John and Frances Rivington, London, 1300 pp." type="book" year="1768">Miller (1768)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
transferred 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1AFF9416CDD67CFBA8F8D0" authority="Linnaeus (1753: 1001)" authorityName="Linnaeus (1753:" authorityPageNumber="1001" authorityYear="1001" box="[700,1096,1828,1855]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picea">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1AFF9416CDD67CFCA1F8D0" box="[700,833,1829,1854]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Pinus picea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1AFF941739D67DFBA8F8D0" author="Linnaeus, C." box="[840,1096,1828,1855]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" refId="ref10121" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1753) Species Plantarum 2. Impensis Laurentii Salvii, Stockholm, 630 pp." type="book" year="1753">Linnaeus (1753: 1001)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
to his new genus as 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1AFF941145D67DFEFCF88C" authority="Miller (1768" authorityName="Miller, Herb. Clifford" authorityYear="1768" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1AFF941145D67DFA4CF8D0" box="[1332,1452,1828,1854]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Abies alba</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1AFF9414F9D611FEFCF88C" author="Miller, P." box="[136,284,1864,1890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" refId="ref10389" refString="Miller, P. (1768) The gardeners dictionary, eighth edition. John and Frances Rivington, London, 1300 pp." type="book" year="1768">Miller (1768</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1AFF941556D611FE77F88D" authority="No." authorityName="No." box="[295,407,1864,1891]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1AFF941556D611FE85F88C" box="[295,357,1864,1890]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Abies</emphasis>
No.
</taxonomicName>
1) (see below). He also included as synonym the Tournefort’s polynomial “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1AFF941080D611FAD5F88C" box="[1265,1333,1864,1890]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Abies</taxonomicName>
laxi folio, fructu surtum spectante” (1700: 585), which was cited by Linnaeus in the protologue.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE921294B1AFF9714CCD6C9FD27FEEE" blockId="1.[136,1452,1828,2071]" lastBlockId="2.[136,1452,158,1085]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
The Linnaeus’s protologue (1753: 1001) of 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1AFF9416DED6C8FCD4F844" authorityName="Linnaeus (1753:" authorityYear="1001" box="[687,820,1937,1962]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picea">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1AFF9416DED6C8FCD4F844" box="[687,820,1937,1962]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Pinus picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
included a nomen specificum legitimum “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1AFF941167D6C9FA8AF844" box="[1302,1386,1936,1962]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">PINUS</taxonomicName>
foliis solitaris emarginatis” followed by four synonyms. The first synonym “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1AFF9417DCD6EDFC11F820" box="[941,1009,1972,1998]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Abies</taxonomicName>
foliis solitariis apice emarginatis” was cited from an earlier Linnaean work (1738: 449), also from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1AFF941750D680FBF4F81C" author="Van Royen, A." box="[801,1044,2008,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" refId="ref12163" refString="Van Royen, A. (1740) Florae Leydensis prodromus. Apud Samuelem Luchtmans, Lugduni Batavorum [Leiden], 538 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 693" type="book" year="1740">van Royen (1740: 89)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1AFF94103BD681FACAF81D" author="Gmelin, J. G." box="[1098,1322,2008,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" refId="ref9398" refString="Gmelin, J. G. (1747) Flora Sibirica, vol. 1. Academiae Scientiarum, St Petersburg, 184 pp. + L Tab. [https: // bibdigital. rjb. csic. es / viewer / 12377 /? offset = 11  page = 306 &amp; viewer = picture &amp; o = bookmark &amp; n = 0 &amp; q =]" type="book" year="1747">Gmelin (1747: 176)</bibRefCitation>
, the second synonym “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1AFF941570D6A5FEA5F7F8" box="[257,325,2044,2070]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Abies</taxonomicName>
laxi folio, fructu surtum spectante” was cited from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1AFF9417EBD6A5FB42F7F9" author="Tournefort, J." box="[922,1186,2044,2071]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" refId="ref11733" refString="Tournefort, J. P de (1700) Institutiones rei herbariae. Tomus primus. Typographia Regia, Paris, 697 + 54 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 154246" type="book" year="1700">Tournefort (1700: 585)</bibRefCitation>
, the third “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1AFF941152D6A5FA87F7F8" box="[1315,1383,2044,2070]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Abies</taxonomicName>
conis surtum spectantibus s.[sive] mas” was cited from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B19FF9716C4D1C7FC73FF57" author="Bauhin, C." box="[693,915,158,185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" refId="ref7533" refString="Bauhin, C. (1623) Pinax theatri botanici. Ludovici Regis, Basel, 522 pp. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 712" type="book" year="1623">Bauhin (1623: 505)</bibRefCitation>
, and the fourth synonym “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B19FF9710CBD1C7FB1EFF56" box="[1210,1278,158,184]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Abies</taxonomicName>
femina s.[sive] Elate teleja” was cited from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B19FF9715B9D19BFCC1FF32" author="Bauhin, C. &amp; Cherler, J. H." box="[456,801,194,221]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" refId="ref7568" refString="Bauhin, C. &amp; Cherler, J. H. (1650) Historia plantarum. Tomus I. Ebroduni, Yverdon, 440 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 146639" type="book" year="1650">Bauhin &amp; Cherler (1650: 231)</bibRefCitation>
. In addition, the protologue includes the locality “ 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B19FF971127D19BFF1AFEEE" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Habitat in Alpibus</emphasis>
Helvetiae, Sueviae, Bavariae, Scothiae”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE921294B19FF9714CCD053FE5FFC8B" blockId="2.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">
Several authors (e.g., do Amaral Franco 1986) consider that the species was described by Miller, and the provenance (or locus classicus) is “… vicinity of Strasbourg and other parts of 
<collectingCountry id="F34161B94B19FF971063D077FB61FEA6" box="[1042,1153,302,328]" name="Germany" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Germany</collectingCountry>
”. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B19FF97117AD077FA46FEA7" author="Miller, P." box="[1291,1446,302,329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" refId="ref10389" refString="Miller, P. (1768) The gardeners dictionary, eighth edition. John and Frances Rivington, London, 1300 pp." type="book" year="1768">Miller (1768)</bibRefCitation>
, in the preface to The gardeners dictionary, ed. 8, stated that he had “now applied Linnaeus’s method entirely except in such particulars…”, of which he gave examples. Concretely, he referred to Linnaean genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B19FF9710D6D02EFB07FE7E" box="[1191,1255,375,400]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B19FF9710D6D02EFB07FE7E" box="[1191,1255,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Pinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[pro parte] under 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B19FF9714F9D0C3FEEAFE5A" authority="Mill." authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1754" box="[136,266,410,436]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B19FF9714F9D0C3FF26FE5A" box="[136,198,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Abies</emphasis>
Mill.
</taxonomicName>
: “Dr. Linnaeus, professor of botany at Upsal, whose system in generally followed at present, ranges this genus in the ninth section of his twenty-first class of plants […]. To this genus he joins the Pine, Cedar, and Larch-tree, supposing them only different species of one genus; however, as there is great difference in the culture of these trees, we shall choose to continue the former method of arranging them under their different genera. It may not be amiss however to observe, that in the former edition of Linnaeus’s Genera Plantarum, these plants were ranged under the article 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B19FF9714A5D317FEF2FD86" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1754" box="[212,274,590,616]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B19FF9714A5D317FEF2FD86" box="[212,274,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Abies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in the last edition he has thought proper to place them under 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B19FF97179BD316FBCAFD86" box="[1002,1066,591,616]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B19FF97179BD316FBCAFD86" box="[1002,1066,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Pinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B19FF971035D317FB2FFD86" author="Miller, P." box="[1092,1231,590,616]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" refId="ref10389" refString="Miller, P. (1768) The gardeners dictionary, eighth edition. John and Frances Rivington, London, 1300 pp." type="book" year="1768">Miller 1768</bibRefCitation>
: [ABI]). The names 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B19FF9714F9D32AFEEBFD62" authorityName="Linnaeus (1753:" authorityYear="1001" box="[136,267,627,652]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picea">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B19FF9714F9D32AFEEBFD62" box="[136,267,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Pinus picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B19FF971531D32BFE57FD62" authorityName="Miller, Herb. Clifford" authorityYear="1768" box="[320,439,626,652]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B19FF971531D32BFE57FD62" box="[320,439,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Abies alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the reference to “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B19FF9716C7D32BFD1AFD62" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1754" box="[694,762,626,652]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Abies</taxonomicName>
taxi folio, fructu fursum spectante” of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B19FF9710DAD32BFA4BFD63" author="Tournefort, J." box="[1195,1451,626,653]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" refId="ref11733" refString="Tournefort, J. P de (1700) Institutiones rei herbariae. Tomus primus. Typographia Regia, Paris, 697 + 54 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 154246" type="book" year="1700">Tournefort (1700: 585)</bibRefCitation>
in common. Therefore, an implicit reference to a Linnaean binomial may be assumed. Thus, the Miller’s binomial 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B19FF9714F9D3E3FF1FFD3A" authorityName="Miller, Herb. Clifford" authorityYear="1768" box="[136,255,698,724]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B19FF9714F9D3E3FF1FFD3A" box="[136,255,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Abies alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is accepted as a replacement name (see 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B19FF9716CED3E2FD0EFD3B" box="[703,750,699,725]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">ICN</emphasis>
Art. 41.3. Ex. 6; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B19FF9717DCD3E3FB67FD3A" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[941,1159,698,724]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" refId="ref11897" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B19FF97107DD3E2FBA4FD3A" box="[1036,1092,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, according to 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B19FF9714F9D386FF57FD17" box="[136,183,735,761]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">ICN</emphasis>
Art. 35.2. Ex. 5. “Combinations validly published. In Linnaeus’s Species plantarum the placing of the epithet in the margin opposite the name of the genus clearly associates the epithet with the name of the genus. The same result is attained in Miller’s The gardeners dictionary, ed. 8, by the inclusion of the epithet in parentheses immediately after the name of the genus [...]”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE921294B19FF9714CCD237FDECFBD3" blockId="2.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">
Among the original elements, an original illustration was published by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B19FF97178AD237FABCFC66" author="Bauhin, C. &amp; Cherler, J. H." box="[1019,1372,878,905]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" refId="ref7568" refString="Bauhin, C. &amp; Cherler, J. H. (1650) Historia plantarum. Tomus I. Ebroduni, Yverdon, 440 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 146639" type="book" year="1650">Bauhin &amp; Cherler (1650: 231)</bibRefCitation>
and is linked to the synonym cited in the protologue by Linnaeus “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B19FF971753D2CBFC86FC42" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1754" box="[802,870,914,940]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Abies</taxonomicName>
femina s.[sive] Elate teleja”. The 
<typeStatus id="54ED9F8B4B19FF971090D2CBFAA8FC42" box="[1249,1352,914,940]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B19FF97111DD2CAFF25FC3E" authorityName="Linnaeus (1753:" authorityYear="1001" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picea">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B19FF97111DD2CAFF25FC3E" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Pinus picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was designated by Farjon &amp; Jarvis (in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B19FF97160BD2EFFCA7FC3E" author="Greuter, W." box="[634,839,950,976]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" refId="ref9642" refString="Greuter, W. (ed.) (1993) NCU- 2. Names in current use in the families Trichocomaceae, Cladoniaceae, Pinaceae, and Lemnaceae. Regnum Vegetabile 128, Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten, 152 pp." type="book" year="1993">Greuter 1993: 110</bibRefCitation>
) from a specimen preserved in the Clifford Herbarium at BM (Herb. Clifford: 449 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B19FF9715CBD283FE18FC1A" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1754" box="[442,504,986,1012]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B19FF9715CBD283FE18FC1A" box="[442,504,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Abies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
2), with barcode BM000647435 (
<figureCitation id="136D3DAC4B19FF971703D283FC52FC1A" box="[882,946,986,1012]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1595,1617]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,187,1568]" captionTargetId="figure-22@3.[340,1247,187,1568]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lectotype of Abies alba Miller, Herb. Clifford: 449, Abies 2, BM (barcode BM000647435). Photography courtesy of Herbarium BM; reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605306" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605306/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B19FF971787D283FB51FC1B" author="Jarvis, C." box="[1014,1201,986,1013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" refId="ref9754" refString="Jarvis, C. (2007) Order out of chaos: Linnaean plant names and their types. Linnean Society of London and the Natural History Museum, London, 1016 pp." type="book" year="2007">Jarvis 2007: 745</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B19FF9710CAD283FA8FFC1B" author="Farjon, A." box="[1211,1391,986,1013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" refId="ref8781" refString="Farjon, A. (2010) A handbook of the world's conifers, vol. 1. Brill Academic Publishers, Leiden &amp; Boston, 1111 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789047430629" type="book" year="2010">Farjon 2010: 59</bibRefCitation>
), this material is linked to the synonym cited by Linnaeus in the protologue as “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B19FF9717A2D2A7FBF7FBF6" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1754" box="[979,1047,1022,1048]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Abies</taxonomicName>
laxi folio, fructu surtum spectante” cited from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B19FF971573D57BFDE7FBD3" author="Tournefort, J." box="[258,519,1058,1085]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" refId="ref11733" refString="Tournefort, J. P de (1700) Institutiones rei herbariae. Tomus primus. Typographia Regia, Paris, 697 + 54 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 154246" type="book" year="1700">Tournefort (1700: 585)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
